<p>
  Creating and modifying content is one of the main features of our
  platform. As a user you can create content and upload it to our
  website so that other users can learn from it.
  <br>
  The content creation dashboard is available from your home page
  on pressing the <code>My Content</code> button. The dashboard has
  been designed with user experience in mind to work like a desktop
  application. You do not need to reload the page to create, modify or
  delete modules and lessons.
  <br>
</p>

<h3 class="subtitle">Modules</h3>

<p>
  Before you create a lesson you must first have a module to store the
  lesson in.
</p>

<h4 class="subsection-title">Creating</h4>

<p>
  To create a new module press the <code>+ Module</code> button below the
  "Modules" heading. This will append a new module to the list below the
  heading. Next, press on the module name (which should be "unnamed").
  You will be presented with the details of the module. Initially,
  it will be unnamed and it will not have a topic or a summary.
</p>

<h4 class="subsection-title">Modifying</h4>

<p>
  To add a name click on the input field below the "Name" heading. You
  will be able to enter a new name. You can also choose a topic for
  the module. You can choose a topic from a drop-down below the "Name"
  section. To change the summary of the module enter a description
  of what the module covers in the large text box below the "Summary"
  heading. Once you are satisfied press <code>Save</code> to apply
  changes.
</p>

